President Biden and First Lady Jill Biden visited Brookland Middle School in Washington, D.C. to address students, parents, and educators about the importance of vaccinations and safety measures in schools during the COVID-19 pandemic. The President shared his personal experience with stuttering and commended students who can speak confidently in public. He emphasized the need for vaccinations for eligible students and urged parents to get their teenagers vaccinated. President Biden also discussed the importance of testing, masking, and ventilation in schools to reduce the spread of the virus. He called for all teachers and staff to be vaccinated and expressed his support for school officials who prioritize the safety of students. The President concluded by urging unity and collaboration in overcoming the challenges posed by the pandemic.